reviews.text: Average hotpot meat quality. The tables by the windows offer a nice view into the streets nearby. Most of the servers are polite. One of them is quite rude and it affected my experience.
Nice food but not enough time to eat
Slightly pricey but is similar to average market price for jp style of all-you-can-eat hotpot, average food quality but the ice cream is surprisingly good
everything is super fresh and the meat is so bloody yum. 11/10 would recommend bc they even have a fairy floss machine
Food quality is good with excellent service.

reviews.text: 餐廳企理，有龐大用餐位置，合和細路女及大人既口味喔。
배가 고파서 아무데나 들어간 건데 양이 많고 맛도 적당했음.
蘿白和牛牛腩又腍又和味，未打火煱已經食了兩碗。
涮涮鍋其實好多，但少有覺得好食，材料新鮮，呢個算一間
差不多每一兩星期就同成班朋友去食，有幾個店員都認得。但今日帶班同事食到尾升，只係淨左少少野係煲諗住唔好浪費食埋，個經理唔知發咩神經話我地再食就加錢，兇神惡煞問我哋你未想加錢，當時我地過左10分鐘，好有禮貌話我地食埋煲入面D野就走，但個經理都係繼續兇我地要加錢！我地就做左次大晒鬼，唔食埋走人，唔係特登浪費，但費事再影響心情！如果咁既態度對客，以後都唔會再介紹朋友，亦無下次！

reviews.text: I rarely leave reviews, but this restaurant deserves it.  We wanted a great meal and almost didn’t go in with 3.5 star review average.  I am so glad we walked in.  The soft shelled crab spring roll starter was excellent.  We had four entrees to share and every one was great.  The curry incorporated cashew which was a nice touch.  The kababs had great flavor.  Service was quick and good.  They only serve beer and wine which is fine, but they lack full bar with cocktails.  If they had a full bar, I would live there!

Love this place. Very good food and very good price
In 2 we took one pad thai and one Vietnamese rice paper roll to share and 2 soda. We spent around 120 hkd each
Nice atmosphere
The food is okay. Not so good. Vietnamese food is great. But this one, could be better if they improve. Wouldn't recommend it to anyone. Sorry.

Saturday afternoon was so hot and humid, it like an oasis for me after hours of shopping Mongkok. I ordered the ice lime soda and a beef pho, the drink arrived first and saved me from dehydration, then the noodle soup came, it looked well and tasted  nice.

The food was tasty; tastier than what we thought it was going to be. We had the Pho, the spring rolls and the seafood and coconut rice. It came out when it was ready and we had more than enough food. 
Service was fine, we were looked after.  We were given a table by the window and able to watch the Friday night madness of Nathan Road.

reviews.text: 位置便利，環境舒適，坐窗邊位看着繁華的彌敦道。招呼到位。點了套餐中的乳豬👍🏼丶米紙卷🙃丶小牛排場河😍，還有飲品及小碗椰汁芒果黑糯米飯做甜品。約$440/2人。
